turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Why did he invite her here?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why does that bother you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She's been in New York three and half years why all of a sudden-

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, maybe he just wanted to see her again.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody comes seven hundred miles just to see.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you mean? He lived next door to the girl all his life, why wouldn't he want to see her again?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Don't look at me like that, he didn't tell me any more than he told you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: He's not going to marry her.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know he's even thinking of it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's got that all about it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well, so what?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What's going on here Joe?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: All right. Now, listen kid-

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: -She's not his girl Joe; she knows she's not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You can't read her mind.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Then why is she still single, I mean New York is full of men, why isn't she married? Probably a hundred people told her she's crazy but she's waited.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How do you know why she has waited?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: She knows what I know, that's why. She's faithful as a rock. In my worst moments I think of her waiting and I know again that I'm right.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look it's a nice day, what are we arguing for?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Nobody in this house dares take her faith away Joe. Strangers might, but not his father, not his brother.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What do you want me to do about it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I want you to act like he's coming back, both of you. Don't you think I haven't noticed since he invited her, I won't stand for any nonsense

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: But Kate

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because if he's not coming back, I'll kill myself. And laugh -- laugh at me but

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: why did that happen the very night she came back she sleeps in his room and suddenly his memorial breaks to pieces, just look at it, look.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I need you to believe with me; I can't stand all alone.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Even last week there was a man who showed up in Detroit missing longer than Larry, you read it yourself.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: All right. All right. Calm yourself.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Just you above all need to believe.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Wait, why my above all?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Don't stop believing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What does that mean, me above all?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Look at you -- look at you shaking.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I can't help it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What have I got to hide? What the hell is the matter with you, Kate?
